  "text": "Each user node chooses a message w ∈ F k p i.i.d. from a uniform distribution over the index set {1, 2, . . . , 2 n R s }. For the ease of simplicity we assume equal message length k at all users, which implies equal secrecy rates for all users. If this is not the case, we would have to extend the nested lattice code chain as described in [CITATION_1] . Each message gets mapped onto a lattice code L = F ∩ V C where the second moment of C equals P such that the power constraint is satisfied. Each user node uses the same codebook",
